text: Karkonosze (, , ) is the highest part of the Sudeten mountains between Silesia and Bohemia. The Schneekoppe, high, is the highest point. This mountain also contain the source of the Elbe River and is also known for the Rübezahl, who is a giant, gnome or mountain spirit. == Other websites == * Official Krkonoše Mts.
